KAB 1340.

460
00:42:09,062 --> 00:42:10,893
Fifty-seven.

461
00:42:14,367 --> 00:42:16,801
From the top of the world...

462
00:42:16,836 --> 00:42:19,896
fabulous 1340.

463
00:42:19,939 --> 00:42:23,501
KAB, Antonio Bay.

464
00:42:25,612 --> 00:42:27,102
Thirty-one.

465
00:42:28,949 --> 00:42:32,908
From the top of the world,
fabulous 1340.

466
00:42:32,953 --> 00:42:39,756
The smooth sound of KAB,
Antonio Bay, California.

467
00:42:42,196 --> 00:42:44,563
Fifty-four.

468
00:42:44,599 --> 00:42:48,831
KAB 1340.

469
00:42:52,774 --> 00:42:55,106
Thirty-one.

470
00:42:55,143 --> 00:42:59,375
The sounds of the surf
from Antonio Bay.

471
00:42:59,414 --> 00:43:03,043
KAB 1340.

472
00:43:05,888 --> 00:43:07,150
Thirty-nine.

473
00:43:07,189 --> 00:43:13,059
Fabulous 1340,
KAB, Antonio Bay.

474
00:43:17,400 --> 00:43:23,236
More music on
top of the world, KAB 1340.

475
00:43:27,744 --> 00:43:32,238
EST-111-B, cut two.

476
00:43:33,917 --> 00:43:35,384
From the top of the world...

477
00:43:35,419 --> 00:43:39,856
fabulous 1340 KAB,
Antonio Bay.

478
00:43:42,559 --> 00:43:45,620
Father, where did you find this?

479
00:43:45,663 --> 00:43:49,360
My grandfather hid his sins
in the walls.

480
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:51,868
When did you find it?

481
00:43:51,903 --> 00:43:55,031
Last night,
just after midnight.

482
00:43:55,073 --> 00:43:56,904
What difference does it make?

483
00:43:56,941 --> 00:43:59,774
That's the same time
the rest of the town fell apart.

484
00:44:04,583 --> 00:44:07,882
And the same time
the six conspirators met...

485
00:44:07,920 --> 00:44:10,320
one hundred years ago.

486
00:44:10,355 --> 00:44:12,482
It's really getting late.

487
00:44:12,524 --> 00:44:15,220
There's not much we can do
about any of this.

488
00:44:15,260 --> 00:44:18,957
Are you going to give
the benediction tonight, Father?

489
00:44:18,997 --> 00:44:22,398
Antonio Bay has a curse on it.

490
00:44:22,434 --> 00:44:24,368
Do we take that as a ''no''?

491
00:44:24,403 --> 00:44:26,599
Maybe it's just as well.

492
00:44:29,042 --> 00:44:32,011
We're leaving now, Father.

493
00:44:32,045 --> 00:44:34,070
Will you be all right?

494
00:44:36,749 --> 00:44:42,085
I'm going to call Dr. Thayden
and ask him to just drop by.

495
00:44:42,122 --> 00:44:45,149
I think you're taking
all of this much too seriously.

496
00:44:45,192 --> 00:44:48,753
We're all cursed,
Mrs. Williams...

497
00:44:48,796 --> 00:44:50,423
all of us.

498
00:45:02,643 --> 00:45:07,911
1340 KAB.

499
00:45:07,949 --> 00:45:10,179
Forty-four.

500
00:45:10,218 --> 00:45:17,124
The smooth sound.
Fabulous 1340 KAB.

501
00:45:23,398 --> 00:45:25,389
Forty-five.

502
00:45:25,433 --> 00:45:31,566
From the top of the world,
fabulous 1340 KAB...

503
00:45:31,607 --> 00:45:35,168
Antonio Bay, California.

504
00:45:35,211 --> 00:45:36,735
Forty-six.

505
00:45:37,914 --> 00:45:40,382
The smooth sound...

506
00:45:41,884 --> 00:45:46,049
Something like
an albatross around the neck...

507
00:45:46,089 --> 00:45:48,557
No. More like a millstone...

508
00:45:48,592 --> 00:45:51,390
a plumbing stone, by God.

509
00:45:51,428 --> 00:45:53,794
Damn them all!

510
00:46:09,514 --> 00:46:11,505
Nine.
Every hour on the hour...

511
00:46:11,549 --> 00:46:13,779
KAB news and weather.

512
00:46:13,818 --> 00:46:15,581
Ten.

513
00:46:15,620 --> 00:46:20,717
Every hour on the hour,
KAB news and weather.

514
00:46:23,061 --> 00:46:26,292
End side two, KAB promos.

515
00:46:37,009 --> 00:46:40,536
How can a man drown
and not touch the water?

516
00:46:40,579 --> 00:46:43,207
He had water in his lungs...

517
00:46:43,249 --> 00:46:46,981
salt water around his mouth,
seaweed in his clothes.

518
00:46:47,020 --> 00:46:49,045
Unless...

519
00:46:51,758 --> 00:46:53,817
You OK?

520
00:46:53,860 --> 00:46:56,727
Did you see his eyes?

521
00:46:56,763 --> 00:46:58,924
Yeah, I saw his eyes.

522
00:47:06,239 --> 00:47:09,073
Andy, the telephone.

523
00:47:09,110 --> 00:47:11,044
I got it, Mrs. Kobritz.

524
00:47:16,484 --> 00:47:18,349
Andy, where did you get
that piece of driftwood?

525
00:47:18,386 --> 00:47:20,980
I told you, Mom.
On the beach this morning.

526
00:47:21,022 --> 00:47:22,512
-Where?
-By the rocks.

527
00:47:22,556 --> 00:47:23,955
What was it doing?

528
00:47:23,991 --> 00:47:25,959
First it was a gold coin...

529
00:47:25,993 --> 00:47:28,087
and then it turned
into the wood.

530
00:47:28,130 --> 00:47:30,189
Andy, I want you
to stay away from the rocks.

531
00:47:30,232 --> 00:47:31,358
Do you understand?

532
00:47:31,400 --> 00:47:33,698
Don't pick up anything else
off the beach.

533
00:47:33,735 --> 00:47:35,202
It didn't belong to anybody.

534
00:47:35,237 --> 00:47:36,864
I know, honey.
It's all right.

535
00:47:36,905 --> 00:47:38,702
I just don't want you
to pick up anything else...

536
00:47:38,740 --> 00:47:40,833
unless you come
and get me first. OK?

537
00:47:40,876 --> 00:47:42,639
OK.

538
00:47:42,678 --> 00:47:44,543
Is Mrs. Kobritz there?

539
00:47:44,579 --> 00:47:46,547
She just came in.

540
00:47:46,581 --> 00:47:50,985
OK. I have to start
the broadcast now.

541
00:47:51,020 --> 00:47:53,420
Andy, promise me you won't
leave the house tonight.

542
00:47:53,456 --> 00:47:55,219
Oh, Mom.

543
00:47:55,258 --> 00:47:57,385
Promise me.

544
00:47:57,427 --> 00:47:59,793
Oh, OK.

545
00:47:59,829 --> 00:48:01,990
I love you, Andy.

546
00:48:02,031 --> 00:48:04,363
Me, too, Mom. Bye.

547
00:48:31,396 --> 00:48:33,057
Ahoy, maties.

548
00:48:33,098 --> 00:48:36,431
This is Stevie Wayne,
your night light...

549
00:48:36,468 --> 00:48:41,428
and KAB, Antonio Bay,
California, is on the air.

550
00:48:41,473 --> 00:48:43,771
I've lined up some tunes
to help you celebrate...

551
00:48:43,808 --> 00:48:46,641
the 100th birthday
of Antonio Bay.

552
00:48:46,678 --> 00:48:50,581
So let's get down to business.

553
00:49:11,938 --> 00:49:14,065
What did your mother want, Andy?

554
00:49:14,107 --> 00:49:15,506
Nothing.

555
00:49:15,542 --> 00:49:17,772
It must have been something.

556
00:49:17,811 --> 00:49:20,405
Nothing.

557
00:49:20,447 --> 00:49:23,883
Mrs. Kobritz,
what are those clouds out there?

558
00:49:30,725 --> 00:49:32,488
Evidence of deep
penetrating wounds...

559
00:49:32,527 --> 00:49:34,017
in each ocular orbit...

560
00:49:34,061 --> 00:49:36,529
entering into
the cranial cavity.

561
00:49:36,564 --> 00:49:39,089
Also jagged lacerations
to the face...

562
00:49:39,133 --> 00:49:40,794
Do you want to wait out front?

563
00:49:40,835 --> 00:49:42,700
I'd rather wait with you.

564
00:49:42,737 --> 00:49:44,102
OK.

565
00:49:44,138 --> 00:49:46,129
Thorax has been crushed...

566
00:49:46,174 --> 00:49:49,508
and the lungs
are filled with fluid.

567
00:49:49,545 --> 00:49:50,705
Talk to you a minute?

568
00:49:58,353 --> 00:50:00,048
She gonna be all right?

569
00:50:00,088 --> 00:50:02,181
-Did you talk to Simms?
-I got him on the radio.

570
00:50:02,224 --> 00:50:04,055
He's coming back
from Bodega Bay.

571
00:50:04,092 --> 00:50:05,559
What the hell
happened out there?

572
00:50:05,594 --> 00:50:07,391
There was rust
all over everything.

573
00:50:07,429 --> 00:50:09,124
It was like the boat had been
out there a long time...

574
00:50:09,164 --> 00:50:10,564
taking on water.

575
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:12,397
He was down below
near the bunks.

576
00:50:12,435 --> 00:50:14,733
Nick, his wounds
are covered with algae...

577
00:50:14,771 --> 00:50:15,897
his lungs are full...

578
00:50:15,939 --> 00:50:17,964
and there's silt
under his fingernails.

579
00:50:18,007 --> 00:50:21,238
I saw Dick Baxter
three days ago in Salinas.

580
00:50:21,277 --> 00:50:22,642
Now he's lying in there
on the table...

581
00:50:22,679 --> 00:50:25,147
looking like he's been
underwater for a month.

582
00:50:47,638 --> 00:50:50,163
-Do you feel that?
-I'll tell you what happens.

583
00:50:50,207 --> 00:50:53,609
-It just got cold in here.
-The water acts like ice.

584
00:51:04,389 --> 00:51:06,880
A whole body would take a year
to decompose...

585
00:51:06,925 --> 00:51:09,393
longer if it was down
far enough, cold enough.

586
00:51:09,427 --> 00:51:11,225
But he was on the boat.

587
00:51:11,264 --> 00:51:12,663
He was below decks.

588
00:51:12,698 --> 00:51:16,691
No. Dick Baxter
died in the ocean.

589
00:51:32,619 --> 00:51:34,746
You remember those three kids
that went diving...

590
00:51:34,788 --> 00:51:37,120
for that old boat off the Point?

591
00:51:37,157 --> 00:51:39,250
We got to them,
they'd been down for a week...

592
00:51:39,293 --> 00:51:40,419
maybe ten days.

593
00:51:40,460 --> 00:51:44,157
I swear to you right now,
he's been down longer.

594
00:53:06,951 --> 00:53:09,317
And while the wrecking
of that beautiful ship...

595
00:53:09,353 --> 00:53:11,651
upon our coast was,
of course...

596
00:53:11,689 --> 00:53:14,716
a tragedy to those
who were on the ship...

597
00:53:14,760 --> 00:53:18,059
it still was the catalyst
that brought together...

598
00:53:18,096 --> 00:53:21,156
all of the people
of this wonderful area.

599
00:53:21,199 --> 00:53:22,598
They came together...

600
00:53:22,634 --> 00:53:26,035
they formed the charter
for Antonio Bay...

601
00:53:26,071 --> 00:53:29,131
the charter by which you have
voted for these councilmen...

602
00:53:29,174 --> 00:53:31,768
who sit on my left
and my right tonight.

603
00:53:33,012 --> 00:53:35,810
The Coast Guard's
looking for them.

604
00:53:35,848 --> 00:53:38,146
They're going to cover the area
pretty good...

605
00:53:38,184 --> 00:53:42,052
so, really,
all we can do is wait.

606
00:53:42,088 --> 00:53:44,249
I understand, Sheriff.

607
00:53:44,290 --> 00:53:45,780
Thank you.

608
00:53:47,560 --> 00:53:49,755
I got to go. I'm up next.

609
00:53:52,933 --> 00:53:55,333
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Williams.

610
00:53:58,372 --> 00:54:01,773
It's funny,
but all I can think about...

611
00:54:01,809 --> 00:54:05,040
is my silly dog
barking all night...

612
00:54:05,079 --> 00:54:10,073
and me just wishing
Al would come home.

613
00:54:12,753 --> 00:54:16,383
Now, we can't have
the chairlady...

614
00:54:16,424 --> 00:54:18,915
of the birthday celebration
in tears, can we?

615
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:20,393
I don't think you ought
to go out there.

616
00:54:20,428 --> 00:54:24,296
I think that's exactly
what I ought to do.

617
00:54:24,332 --> 00:54:26,562
I appreciate
all your help, Nick.

618
00:54:26,601 --> 00:54:27,932
That's all right.

619
00:54:45,988 --> 00:54:48,479
I searched
a long time for this one.

620
00:54:48,524 --> 00:54:50,890
I hope you remember it.

621
00:54:55,298 --> 00:54:57,095
Happy 100th, Antonio Bay.

622
00:54:57,134 --> 00:55:00,501
The ceremonies are underway
at Shelby Square.

623
00:55:00,537 --> 00:55:03,438
And we'll have that candlelight
procession in about an hour.

624
00:55:03,473 --> 00:55:07,204
So if you hurry,
you can still make it.

625
00:55:07,244 --> 00:55:08,711
The Coast Guard
dropped me a note.

626
00:55:08,745 --> 00:55:11,805
They found the ''Sea Grass''
earlier this afternoon...

627
00:55:11,848 --> 00:55:13,338
but there's no further word...

628
00:55:13,383 --> 00:55:17,218
as to the condition of the ship
or the men on-board.

629
00:55:17,255 --> 00:55:20,588
I'll keep you posted
as the news comes in to me.

630
00:55:20,625 --> 00:55:23,458
Hope no one else gets lost
out there in the fog.

631
00:55:27,698 --> 00:55:29,256
I'll be right back.

632
00:55:38,944 --> 00:55:40,571
Hello. My name's Nick Castle.

633
00:55:40,612 --> 00:55:42,409
You don't know me,
but I'm one of the men...

634
00:55:42,447 --> 00:55:44,347
who found the ''Sea Grass''
this afternoon.

635
00:55:44,383 --> 00:55:46,681
I'm sorry.
I don't have any further word.

636
00:55:46,718 --> 00:55:49,084
I understand.
That's not what I called about.

637
00:55:49,121 --> 00:55:52,852
You just mentioned something
now on the radio about the fog.

638
00:56:01,634 --> 00:56:06,196
This is going to sound
a little strange, but...

639
00:56:06,239 --> 00:56:08,139
I saw the fog last night...

640
00:56:08,174 --> 00:56:09,698
out in the ocean
in the distance.

641
00:56:09,742 --> 00:56:12,540
It was...glowing.

642
00:56:18,686 --> 00:56:19,812
What seemed to be happening...

643
00:56:19,854 --> 00:56:21,879
is that the wind
was moving due east...

644
00:56:21,922 --> 00:56:24,220
and the fog
just kept moving west.

645
00:56:24,258 --> 00:56:25,782
I know that sounds
completely crazy.

646
00:56:25,826 --> 00:56:27,259
Right now it doesn't.

647
00:56:27,294 --> 00:56:29,455
Something happened last night.

648
00:56:29,496 --> 00:56:31,225
At the same time
that fog was moving in...

649
00:56:31,265 --> 00:56:33,256
this whole town went unglued.

650
00:56:33,300 --> 00:56:34,767
Hold on.

651
00:56:38,740 --> 00:56:41,231
I've got some more
birthday music for you...

652
00:56:41,276 --> 00:56:43,141
and a few other surprises.

653
00:56:43,178 --> 00:56:46,443
Then I'll be ready to check in
with the weatherman.

654
00:56:46,481 --> 00:56:49,939
And the weatherman will be
ready to check in with you.

655
00:57:00,763 --> 00:57:02,731
-Hello?
-I'm still here.

656
00:57:02,765 --> 00:57:04,096
There's one other thing.

657
00:57:04,133 --> 00:57:06,863
It may have nothing
to do with the ''Sea Grass''.

658
00:57:06,903 --> 00:57:08,962
Anything.

659
00:57:09,005 --> 00:57:12,736
My son found a piece
of driftwood this morning.

660
00:57:18,582 --> 00:57:21,813
Hey, Mel. How you doing?

661
00:57:21,852 --> 00:57:25,049
Your girlfriend on the radio
has been talking about you.

662
00:57:25,088 --> 00:57:27,056
I came in tonight
just to keep her happy.

663
00:57:27,090 --> 00:57:28,682
I thought
you were off tonight.

664
00:57:28,725 --> 00:57:29,885
I love my job.

665
00:57:29,927 --> 00:57:33,226
You can tell them all
about that big fog bank...

666
00:57:33,263 --> 00:57:34,924
moving in
the southeast there.

667
00:57:34,965 --> 00:57:37,560
-Where?
-You'll see it.

668
00:57:37,602 --> 00:57:39,570
I'm on my way.
See you tomorrow.

669
00:57:39,604 --> 00:57:41,595
Yeah, Mel. I'll see you.

670
00:57:51,482 --> 00:57:53,006
There you are.

671
00:58:03,028 --> 00:58:04,620
I've got to make a run
out to the lighthouse...

672
00:58:04,663 --> 00:58:06,187
at Spivey Point.
Want to come?

673
00:58:06,231 --> 00:58:07,493
-Sure.
-Come on.

674
00:58:13,238 --> 00:58:14,637
Hi, sweetheart!

675
00:58:14,673 --> 00:58:15,901
I thought you were celebrating.

676
00:58:15,941 --> 00:58:18,740
I couldn't spend an evening
without you.

677
00:58:18,778 --> 00:58:21,440
I'm up in about thirty seconds.
What's new?

678
00:58:21,481 --> 00:58:23,642
Another fog bank.

679
00:58:23,683 --> 00:58:25,116
Where?

680
00:58:25,151 --> 00:58:27,415
It's coming in off the ocean
from the southeast.

681
00:58:27,454 --> 00:58:29,217
It's heading inland.
It should be here...

682
00:58:29,255 --> 00:58:30,950
at the weather station
in ten minutes.

683
00:58:30,991 --> 00:58:33,551
Dan, hold on.

684
00:58:34,894 --> 00:58:36,953
I have a special
weather bulletin.

685
00:58:36,998 --> 00:58:38,556
The tri-county
weather station...

686
00:58:38,599 --> 00:58:41,966
reports a fog bank moving
southeast along the coast.

687
00:58:42,003 --> 00:58:43,698
For whoever's interested...

688
00:58:43,738 --> 00:58:47,071
that's the weather station
on Old Russellville Road.

689
00:58:47,108 --> 00:58:51,101
Repeating--a fog bank is moving
southwest along the coast...

690
00:58:51,145 --> 00:58:54,273
toward the weather station
on Old Russellville Road.

691
00:58:59,087 --> 00:59:00,918
Dan, are you still there?

692
00:59:00,956 --> 00:59:03,254
I'm still here.

693
00:59:03,291 --> 00:59:05,316
You sound different tonight...

694
00:59:05,360 --> 00:59:07,385
kind of intense.

695
00:59:07,429 --> 00:59:10,057
I just feel like talking,
that's all.

696
00:59:10,098 --> 00:59:12,396
You told me you didn't like
to talk on the telephone...

697
00:59:12,434 --> 00:59:14,231
because you talked
on the radio all day.

698
00:59:14,269 --> 00:59:15,463
Dan, where's the fog now?

699
00:59:15,504 --> 00:59:18,406
It should be
right outside my door now.

700
00:59:21,577 --> 00:59:23,374
Hold on.
I'm going to try something.

701
00:59:28,951 --> 00:59:30,145
I can see it.

702
00:59:30,186 --> 00:59:32,916
Now, what is the big deal?

703
00:59:32,955 --> 00:59:35,014
You've seen fog once,
you seen it for life.

704
00:59:35,058 --> 00:59:37,083
There's something
different about this fog.

705
00:59:37,126 --> 00:59:39,925
It glows.
Can't you see anything yet?

706
00:59:39,963 --> 00:59:43,421
Glows? Oh, I get it.

707
00:59:43,467 --> 00:59:45,435
You take something
to keep you going, right?

708
00:59:45,469 --> 00:59:48,131
Does it make you feel
a little weird sometimes?

709
00:59:49,306 --> 00:59:52,104
-Hey.
-What?

710
00:59:52,142 --> 00:59:54,110
The lights went out.

711
00:59:54,144 --> 00:59:57,443
Everything's going crazy.

712
00:59:57,481 --> 00:59:59,882
Barometer's falling,
temperature's dropping.

713
00:59:59,918 --> 01:00:01,886
Dan, what is it?

714
01:00:01,920 --> 01:00:03,319
What the hell's that?

715
01:00:03,354 --> 01:00:05,049
Dan, what is it?
What's happening?

716
01:00:05,090 --> 01:00:07,558
What is it?
What's happening?

717
01:00:07,592 --> 01:00:10,060
Someone's shining a light
through the window.

718
01:00:10,095 --> 01:00:11,392
Dan, listen to me.

719
01:00:11,429 --> 01:00:14,262
Hold on, sweetheart.
I want to check this out.

720
01:00:17,102 --> 01:00:20,231
Dan, stay on the phone!

721
01:00:31,684 --> 01:00:33,584
This has got to be a joke.

722
01:00:38,557 --> 01:00:41,083
Someone's at the front door,
sweetheart...

723
01:00:41,128 --> 01:00:42,993
playing a stupid joke.

724
01:00:43,029 --> 01:00:45,725
And whoever it is...

725
01:00:45,765 --> 01:00:48,063
they ain't gonna like
finding me home.

726
01:00:48,101 --> 01:00:49,898
Dan, stay away from the door!

727
01:01:06,787 --> 01:01:08,084
Anybody here?

728
01:01:11,592 --> 01:01:13,890
Some asshole got drunk
and started taking...

729
01:01:13,928 --> 01:01:16,692
this 100-year-old business
too seriously.

730
01:02:09,653 --> 01:02:13,714
And so all of us living here
in Antonio Bay today...

731
01:02:13,757 --> 01:02:15,884
owe a great debt
of gratitude...

732
01:02:15,926 --> 01:02:18,360
to those men and women
a hundred years ago...

733
01:02:18,395 --> 01:02:21,559
who struggled and sacrificed
to make this town grow...

734
01:02:21,600 --> 01:02:23,295
into what it is today.

735
01:02:23,335 --> 01:02:27,795
And it's up to us to keep
their kind of spirit alive.

736
01:02:32,777 --> 01:02:34,005
I have an urgent bulletin.

737
01:02:34,045 --> 01:02:37,776
Will Sheriff David Simms please
contact KAB Radio immediately?

738
01:02:37,816 --> 01:02:40,877
The number is 555-2131.

739
01:02:40,920 --> 01:02:42,649
This is an emergency.

740
01:02:44,824 --> 01:02:49,158
So we must redouble our efforts,
work together.

741
01:02:49,195 --> 01:02:51,720
We have a vital,
thriving community.

742
01:02:51,764 --> 01:02:54,232
And I say
we have to keep it that way.

743
01:02:57,370 --> 01:02:59,304
This is an emergency.

744
01:02:59,338 --> 01:03:02,797
Sheriff David Simms,
please contact KAB immediately.

745
01:03:02,843 --> 01:03:06,574
555-2131.
This is an emergency.

746
01:03:21,729 --> 01:03:22,923
Sheriff Simms?

747
01:03:28,903 --> 01:03:30,734
And so, as we make our way...

748
01:03:30,772 --> 01:03:32,433
to the presentation
of the statue...

749
01:03:32,473 --> 01:03:34,771
I think we should all
keep in mind...

750
01:03:34,809 --> 01:03:36,401
the significance
of this night...

751
01:03:36,444 --> 01:03:38,776
for every citizen
of Antonio Bay.

752
01:04:26,997 --> 01:04:30,763
We should all proceed
over to the statue.

753
01:04:30,801 --> 01:04:32,860
Single file. Don't push.

754
01:04:32,903 --> 01:04:34,495
Take your time.

755
01:05:00,732 --> 01:05:02,701
Start!

756
01:05:02,735 --> 01:05:04,726
Please start!

757
01:05:09,108 --> 01:05:10,871
Why did all the lights go out?

758
01:05:10,910 --> 01:05:15,847
One of the lines
are probably down, Andy.

759
01:05:15,882 --> 01:05:19,579
They usually take care
of these things right away.

760
01:05:19,619 --> 01:05:22,315
I think it's kind of neat.

761
01:05:49,617 --> 01:05:51,482
What's that now?

762
01:06:08,037 --> 01:06:09,561
Start!

763
01:06:15,311 --> 01:06:17,711
Andy! Andy,
get out of the house!

764
01:06:17,746 --> 01:06:20,078
Mrs. Kobritz, get him
out of the house! Please! Run!

765
01:06:20,115 --> 01:06:23,050
I think maybe we better
close all the windows, Andy.

766
01:06:23,085 --> 01:06:24,781
Are your bedroom windows
closed?

767
01:06:24,821 --> 01:06:26,083
I'll go see.

768
01:06:34,965 --> 01:06:37,399
Someone listen to me!
My son is trapped!

769
01:06:37,434 --> 01:06:40,403
887 White Beach Lane!
My son is trapped by the fog!

770
01:06:40,437 --> 01:06:42,735
Andy, get out of the house!
Run!

771
01:06:47,278 --> 01:06:50,304
Wow! Look at that!

772
01:06:50,348 --> 01:06:52,111
Are your windows all closed?

773
01:06:52,149 --> 01:06:53,480
Yes, ma'am.

774
01:06:53,518 --> 01:06:55,076
What about
your mother's bedroom?

775
01:07:06,832 --> 01:07:09,892
Please, someone!
My son is trapped!

776
01:07:12,471 --> 01:07:14,371
Andy, run! Run!

777
01:07:14,406 --> 01:07:16,670
Mrs. Kobritz, run!

778
01:07:19,711 --> 01:07:22,509
Andy, I want you
to go to your room.

779
01:07:22,548 --> 01:07:24,106
I think I should stay.

780
01:07:24,149 --> 01:07:26,516
-Right now.
-Yes.

781
01:07:47,575 --> 01:07:48,803
Go to your room.

782
01:07:48,842 --> 01:07:50,503
I want to see who it is.

783
01:07:51,912 --> 01:07:53,937
Can't I stay
for two more seconds?

784
01:07:56,917 --> 01:07:59,545
OK, I'm going.

785
01:08:13,401 --> 01:08:15,392
Mrs. Kobritz?

786
01:08:25,448 --> 01:08:27,780
Please. My son is trapped!

787
01:08:27,817 --> 01:08:31,719
887 White Beach Lane.

788
01:08:31,754 --> 01:08:34,348
Someone get
to 887 White Beach Lane.

789
01:08:47,104 --> 01:08:50,904
My son is trapped!
Get him out of the fog!

790
01:08:57,614 --> 01:08:59,605
Please, someone!

791
01:09:00,884 --> 01:09:02,442
My son is trapped!

792
01:09:11,396 --> 01:09:13,296
Come on!
Get out of there, now!

793
01:09:22,173 --> 01:09:24,869
Andy, run! Run!

794
01:09:27,479 --> 01:09:29,344
Come on! Come on.

795
01:09:29,381 --> 01:09:31,144
Go! Go!

796
01:09:43,429 --> 01:09:44,691
Come on!

797
01:09:44,730 --> 01:09:47,996
Don't pop it.
Try to ease it out.

798
01:09:48,034 --> 01:09:49,592
Oh, Jesus.

799
01:09:55,675 --> 01:09:57,233
Come on, baby!

800
01:09:57,277 --> 01:10:00,735
Come on. It'll go.

801
01:10:00,780 --> 01:10:01,940
Reverse! Reverse!

802
01:10:01,981 --> 01:10:03,414
Come on!

803
01:10:10,458 --> 01:10:12,323
Come on, do it! Do it!

804
01:10:37,285 --> 01:10:39,310
...Stevie Wayne
for the last twenty minutes.

805
01:10:39,521 --> 01:10:41,785
I think it's best
we call it a night here.

806
01:10:41,823 --> 01:10:43,290
Another five or ten minutes...

807
01:10:43,325 --> 01:10:45,122
everyone will have
seen the statue.

808
01:10:45,160 --> 01:10:47,629
All right, but let's get them
through as quickly as we can.

809
01:10:47,663 --> 01:10:50,131
Probably be a good idea
if you went home, Kathy.

810
01:10:50,166 --> 01:10:51,793
We can close up here.

811
01:10:51,834 --> 01:10:53,131
I should see it through
to the end.

812
01:10:53,169 --> 01:10:55,467
Mrs. Williams,
there's nothing more to do here.

813
01:10:55,505 --> 01:10:57,871
Let me take you home.

814
01:10:57,907 --> 01:11:00,740
A little annoying,
but you're right.

815
01:11:00,777 --> 01:11:02,904
-Would you please take me?
-Yes, ma'am.

816
01:11:02,945 --> 01:11:05,607
-I'll call you tomorrow.
-Thank you.

817
01:11:10,354 --> 01:11:12,720
Andy, I don't even know
if you can hear me.

818
01:11:12,756 --> 01:11:14,849
I'm sorry that
I didn't come for you...

819
01:11:14,892 --> 01:11:16,052
that I wasn't there.

820
01:11:17,461 --> 01:11:19,952
Andy, please understand.

821
01:11:21,799 --> 01:11:24,632
I have to stay here.

822
01:11:35,580 --> 01:11:39,846
The fog is moving inland...

823
01:11:39,884 --> 01:11:41,784
away from the beach...

824
01:11:44,389 --> 01:11:46,323
towards Antonio Bay.

825
01:11:52,298 --> 01:11:54,459
It's over by the armory.

826
01:11:54,500 --> 01:11:57,230
I can't remember the name.

827
01:11:57,269 --> 01:12:00,067
No, no--
I think it's Chestnut.

828
01:12:04,844 --> 01:12:07,904
Feel like listening
to some music?

829
01:12:07,947 --> 01:12:10,439
Sure.

830
01:12:10,483 --> 01:12:12,348
It's moving faster now.

831
01:12:12,385 --> 01:12:13,875
Up Regent Avenue.

832
01:12:13,920 --> 01:12:15,911
Up to the end
of Smallhouse Road.

833
01:12:15,956 --> 01:12:17,389
What is that?

834
01:12:20,093 --> 01:12:22,653
It's just hitting
the outskirts of town.

835
01:12:22,696 --> 01:12:24,687
Broad Street.

836
01:12:26,132 --> 01:12:28,623
Clay Street.

837
01:12:54,997 --> 01:12:56,828
It's moving down 10th Street.

838
01:12:56,865 --> 01:13:00,323
Get inside and lock your doors.
Close your windows.

839
01:13:00,369 --> 01:13:02,599
There's something in the fog.

840
01:13:09,177 --> 01:13:11,510
If you're on the south side
of town, go north.

841
01:13:11,547 --> 01:13:13,515
Stay away from the fog.

842
01:13:21,925 --> 01:13:24,018
Richardsville Pike
up to Beacon Hill...

843
01:13:24,060 --> 01:13:26,426
is the only clear road.

844
01:13:26,462 --> 01:13:28,430
Up to the church.

845
01:13:28,464 --> 01:13:31,559
If you can get out of town,
get to the old church.

846
01:13:39,410 --> 01:13:41,844
Now the junction at 101
is cut off.

847
01:13:41,879 --> 01:13:45,337
If you can get out of town,
get to the old church.

848
01:13:45,382 --> 01:13:47,282
It's the only place
left to go.

849
01:13:47,318 --> 01:13:50,152
Get to the old church
on Beacon Hill.

850
01:13:58,330 --> 01:14:00,127
-It cut us off!
-Where is it?

851
01:14:00,165 --> 01:14:01,894
-Right behind us.
-Quick, inside.

852
01:14:05,370 --> 01:14:07,065
Come on.

853
01:14:07,105 --> 01:14:08,265
Hurry.

854
01:14:10,141 --> 01:14:13,077
Father, is there a basement
or cellar in here?

855
01:14:13,112 --> 01:14:15,137
-We can't hide any longer.
-We have to try!

856
01:14:15,181 --> 01:14:17,115
No matter where we go,
it will find us.

857
01:14:21,554 --> 01:14:23,249
Is there a basement
or cellar here?

858
01:14:23,289 --> 01:14:25,257
There's a study in back.
I'll show you the way.

859
01:14:25,291 --> 01:14:26,724
Come on. Hurry.

860
01:14:26,759 --> 01:14:29,125
Give me that.

861
01:14:58,192 --> 01:15:00,126
The fog is sweeping inland.

862
01:15:01,629 --> 01:15:04,462
It's almost like a wall
across the east end of town.

863
01:15:29,058 --> 01:15:30,923
Blake and his men
have come for us.

864
01:15:30,959 --> 01:15:32,552
-Who's Blake?
-It's in the journal.

865
01:15:32,595 --> 01:15:33,721
-What journal?
-I don't know.

866
01:15:33,763 --> 01:15:36,061
-We're cursed.
-What are you talking about?

867
01:15:36,099 --> 01:15:39,296
-Where is the journal?
-It's in there.

868
01:15:45,375 --> 01:15:46,706
Over by the window?

869
01:15:46,743 --> 01:15:49,769
-It can do us no good now.
-It's all we got.

870
01:15:49,813 --> 01:15:51,508
If anything happens,
just lock the door.

871
01:15:51,548 --> 01:15:53,881
Get back. Shut the door.

872
01:16:34,127 --> 01:16:35,321
''Six must die.''

873
01:16:35,361 --> 01:16:36,623
The three men
on the ''Sea Grass''.

874
01:16:36,662 --> 01:16:38,254
And the weatherman is four.

875
01:16:38,297 --> 01:16:39,764
-Mrs. Kobritz.
-Yeah, five.

876
01:16:39,799 --> 01:16:41,266
And one of us makes six.

877
01:16:41,300 --> 01:16:42,927
That's what they want.
They've come back...

878
01:16:42,969 --> 01:16:44,596
for the six
original conspirators.

879
01:16:44,637 --> 01:16:46,070
There must be something
in here!

880
01:16:46,105 --> 01:16:47,595
It's me they want.
I am the sixth!

881
01:16:47,640 --> 01:16:48,766
Why would they want you?

882
01:16:48,808 --> 01:16:50,105
Wait, Father.
You didn't read us this.

883
01:16:50,143 --> 01:16:52,111
''Were it possible
to raise the dead...

884
01:16:52,145 --> 01:16:54,444
''I would return Blake's fortune
to him intact...

885
01:16:54,481 --> 01:16:57,416
''save the money spent
on these walls that hide it.''

886
01:16:57,451 --> 01:16:59,351
''My fellow conspirators
believe...

887
01:16:59,386 --> 01:17:01,377
''that the confiscated fortune
has been stolen...

888
01:17:01,421 --> 01:17:04,049
''from them, when in fact,
I am the thief...

889
01:17:04,091 --> 01:17:06,559
''and God's temple
is the tomb of gold.''

890
01:17:06,593 --> 01:17:10,120
''I am the thief,
and God's temple--''

891
01:17:11,999 --> 01:17:14,195
Now, wait. Get rid of that.

892
01:17:15,803 --> 01:17:18,363
Get out of the way!

893
01:17:39,495 --> 01:17:42,931
-Give me a hand.
-Andy, stay right there.

894
01:18:06,623 --> 01:18:08,318
The gold.

895
01:18:27,245 --> 01:18:29,543
He melted down the gold
into this.

896
01:18:33,618 --> 01:18:35,484
Somebody help her!

897
01:18:48,634 --> 01:18:50,397
Don't go in there!

898
01:19:31,312 --> 01:19:34,179
Blake, I have your gold.

899
01:19:41,589 --> 01:19:42,749
Blake?

900
01:20:20,831 --> 01:20:22,765
This is your gold, Blake.

901
01:20:22,799 --> 01:20:26,166
My grandfather stole it
from you.

902
01:20:28,205 --> 01:20:31,003
I'm the one
who must answer for it.

903
01:20:43,688 --> 01:20:46,680
I'm the sixth conspirator.

904
01:20:48,693 --> 01:20:51,821
I'm Father Malone.

905
01:20:51,863 --> 01:20:54,024
Take me.

906
01:21:50,391 --> 01:21:52,188
Father Malone!

907
01:24:11,872 --> 01:24:13,237
Look.

908
01:24:23,485 --> 01:24:25,146
It's going away.

909
01:25:01,125 --> 01:25:04,561
I don't know what happened
to Antonio Bay tonight.

910
01:25:04,595 --> 01:25:07,928
Something came out of the fog...

911
01:25:07,965 --> 01:25:10,866
and tried to destroy us.

912
01:25:10,901 --> 01:25:13,927
In one moment, it vanished.

913
01:25:13,971 --> 01:25:17,463
But if this has been
anything but a nightmare...

914
01:25:17,508 --> 01:25:21,377
and if we don't wake up to find
ourselves safe in our beds...

915
01:25:21,413 --> 01:25:25,179
it could come again.

916
01:25:25,216 --> 01:25:28,652
To the ships at sea
who can hear my voice...

917
01:25:28,687 --> 01:25:32,919
look across the water
into the darkness.

918
01:25:34,325 --> 01:25:36,486
Look for the fog.

919
01:26:04,991 --> 01:26:08,119
Why not six, Blake?

920
01:26:10,630 --> 01:26:12,723
Why not me?

921
